modules.description: Provides functions to configure endpoints for sending traces, metrics, and logs, along with batching parameters and timeouts. Works with strings for URLs, lists of headers, and optional integers for batch sizes and timeouts. Used to set up observability pipelines with custom endpoints and batch processing rules.

Provides functions for creating and managing traces, spans, and metrics, with support for exporting data via HTTP using Protobuf. Works with types such as trace IDs, span contexts, and metric values. Used to integrate server applications with observability backends like Jaeger and Datadog.

Configures observability pipelines by defining endpoints for traces, metrics, and logs, with control over batching and timeouts. Accepts URL strings, header lists, and optional integers to shape data transmission. Enables custom routing of telemetry data with specified processing rules. Examples include setting up a trace endpoint with a 100-item batch and 500ms timeout, or adding authentication headers to metric uploads.
